For an infinite point source emitting S neutrons per second isotropically in an infinite diffusing medium, the source condition used to determine the constants in the diffusion equation solution involves the limit of the product of the radial distance squared and the neutron current density as the radial distance approaches zero. Which of the following correctly represents this source condition?
A: \lim_{r\to 0} J(r) = \frac{S}{4\pi}
B: \lim_{r\to 0} r J(r) = \frac{S}{4\pi}
C: \lim_{r\to 0} r^2 J(r) = \frac{S}{4\pi}
D: \lim_{r\to 0} r^2 \phi(r) = \frac{S}{4\pi D}
